'''Cao Zhiyun''' ({{zh|t=曹志耘|s=曹志耘|p=Cáo Zhìyún}}), born in [[Jinhua]], Zhejiang in 1961<ref>{{cite web|last=BLCU |title=曹志耘教授 |url=http://www.blcu.edu.cn/yjsedu/up/zhaosheng/daoshijianjie/%E6%9B%B9%E5%BF%97%E8%80%98.htm |accessdate=13 June 2011 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20111002152929/http://www.blcu.edu.cn/yjsedu/up/zhaosheng/daoshijianjie/%E6%9B%B9%E5%BF%97%E8%80%98.htm |archivedate=2 October 2011 |df= }}</ref> is a Chinese linguist and dialectologist and is a professor at [[Beijing Language and Culture University]]. He is most well known for his work as the primary editor of the groundbreaking 2008 ''[[Linguistic Atlas of Chinese Dialects]]'' but has made numerous other significant contributions to Chinese dialectology with a focus on the Southern [[Wu Chinese|Wu]] varieties in and around his native [[Jinhua]]. Despite his focus, his works exhibit an all around thorough and in-depth understanding of all Chinese dialect families and contemporary linguistics and is widely regarded in the field as one of China's leading authorities on Chinese dialectology.
