{{Infobox language |name=Nyamwezi |region=[[Tanzania]] |ethnicity=[[Nyamwezi people|Nyamwezi]] |speakers= {{sigfig|1.03|2}} million |date=2006 |ref=e18 |familycolor=Niger-Congo |fam2=[[Atlantic–Congo languages|Atlantic–Congo]] |fam3=[[Benue–Congo languages|Benue–Congo]] |fam4=[[Southern Bantoid languages|Southern Bantoid]] |fam5=[[Bantu languages|Bantu]] |fam6=[[Northeast Bantu]] |fam7=Takama |fam8=Sukuma |iso2=nym |lc1=nym|ld1=Nyamwezi |lc2=kcz|ld2=Konongo |guthrie=F.22 |glotto=nyam1276 |glottoname=Nyamwezi |glotto2=kono1265 |glottoname2=Konongo }}
'''Nyamwezi''' is a major [[Bantu language]] of central [[Tanzania]]. It forms a [[dialect continuum]] with [[Sukuma language|Sukuma]], but is more distinct from other neighboring languages.
